channel.title: Why does this happen?!
channel.description:
Ok in runserver when ppl try to get on it does this,
[code]ClientHandler: Accepted from c-76-101-56-5.hsd1.fl.comcast.net:1712[/code]
and it dont let them log in also adds nulls. I also know its supposed to say
[code] ClientHandler: Accepted from c-76-101-56-5.hsd1.fl.comcast.net:1712 blooddogg is signing onto server.[/code]
BUT IT DON'T :(

item.title: Why does this happen?!
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

bakatool:

thats how server crash -.- … with a server crasher

Exactly…

montalvom, your server is either:

  1. Being crashed.
  2. Being checked by a server status
  3. Being pinged a lot (doesnt have to be a crasher)

It’s quite obvious really. If you see a host get accepted, but nobody logs in, you know its not a real person and you know you’re being pinged or something similiar.
